title: Girls Soccer: Red Bank Catholic’s Jackie Robinson has “best hands” in the Shore
text:
MORE TINTON FALLS - For the last four years, the Red Bank Catholic girls soccer team hasn’t worried about who would be their goalie.
The answer was always the same. It was Jackie Robinson.
GETTING THAT FIRST OPPORTUNITY
Robinson, now a senior, has led the Caseys this season to a 9-6-2 overall record and a 7-4-1 Class B North record as of Oct. 20th. Also, Red Bank Catholic is the No. 15 seed in this year's Shore Conference Tournament and they'll host No. 18 seed Freehold in a preliminary round game. Robinson has made over 70 career starts and still remembers her first opportunity to be in goal for the Caseys.
